        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 8:48AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 848 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles west of Vandervoort, or 21 miles southwest of Mena, moving east
at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shady Lake Recreation Area...     Cossatot River State Park...
Hatton...                         Wickes...
Hartley...                        Cove...
Grannis...                        Mccauley...
Bogg Springs...                   Vandervoort...
Hatfield...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
